This paper is about natural language processing (NLP), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) that deals with the interaction between computers and human language. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses word vectors, which are a type of machine learning model used in NLP, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the historical development of word vectors, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper briefly touches on the use of word vectors in computer vision, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
